1
00:00:26,750 --> 00:00:27,916
Cut!

2
00:00:28,708 --> 00:00:31,000
-Aqua!
-Is he okay?

3
00:00:31,083 --> 00:00:32,166
Aqua.

4
00:00:37,208 --> 00:00:38,625
I still sense it.

5
00:00:39,208 --> 00:00:42,291
The smell of blood like rusted metal

6
00:00:43,208 --> 00:00:44,791
clinging to me forever.

7
00:00:48,666 --> 00:00:51,791
I feel her hand growing colder.

8
00:00:53,041 --> 00:00:54,541
I can't forget it.

9
00:00:58,875 --> 00:01:00,625
It's all your fault.

10
00:01:08,583 --> 00:01:13,083
If you'd put your body on the line
to protect her...

11
00:01:19,083 --> 00:01:20,208
Are you okay?

12
00:01:23,958 --> 00:01:27,416
They'll reshoot your scene another day.

13
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:29,333
Today, just get some rest.

14
00:01:30,791 --> 00:01:33,541
Want someone from home to pick you up?

15
00:01:36,041 --> 00:01:37,208
Please don't.

16
00:01:37,583 --> 00:01:38,583
Why not?

17
00:01:40,958 --> 00:01:42,833
I don't want Ruby knowing.

18
00:01:46,083 --> 00:01:48,708
GOTANDA STUDIO

19
00:01:55,291 --> 00:01:59,500
Since when did I become your
personal chauffeur?

20
00:01:59,583 --> 00:02:02,083
I'm gonna lie down upstairs.

21
00:02:06,375 --> 00:02:09,375
His impudence never ceases to amaze.

22
00:02:10,791 --> 00:02:12,625
Sorry to put you out.

23
00:02:12,708 --> 00:02:14,208
Don't sweat it.

24
00:02:14,833 --> 00:02:17,833
I'm the only one who knows his deal.

25
00:02:18,250 --> 00:02:19,583
Take a seat.

26
00:02:19,958 --> 00:02:20,958
Okay.

27
00:02:24,666 --> 00:02:26,958
-Here.
-Thank you.

28
00:02:31,875 --> 00:02:33,333
How'd it happen?

29
00:02:34,791 --> 00:02:39,125
Shooting a scene where he loses
his best friend.

30
00:02:39,208 --> 00:02:43,125
The director kept asking him
to show more emotion.

31
00:02:44,916 --> 00:02:46,458
That would do it.

32
00:02:49,625 --> 00:02:52,458
What's your relationship to Aqua?

33
00:02:53,291 --> 00:02:54,666
Girlfriend?

34
00:02:56,500 --> 00:02:57,541
As it were.

35
00:03:00,208 --> 00:03:03,416
He gets around more than I thought.

36
00:03:04,791 --> 00:03:08,666
I suppose his girlfriend
has a right to know.

37
00:03:12,583 --> 00:03:16,125
What you saw today... Aqua collapsing.

38
00:03:16,458 --> 00:03:18,541
It isn't the first time.

39
00:03:18,625 --> 00:03:20,875
Panic attack, isn't it?

40
00:03:21,291 --> 00:03:22,416
Yeah.

41
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:28,625
As a child, he witnessed
a terrible incident.

42
00:03:29,583 --> 00:03:33,333
When that memory is sparked,
this is what happens.

43
00:03:34,166 --> 00:03:37,333
In short, he experiences PTSD.

44
00:03:40,375 --> 00:03:43,416
He spent years in counseling over it,

45
00:03:43,958 --> 00:03:47,416
but he tired of worrying his family.

46
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:49,541
So he feigned being cured.

47
00:03:54,125 --> 00:03:56,708
But it's not something you forget.

48
00:03:57,875 --> 00:04:00,208
I'm still not over it myself.

49
00:04:01,708 --> 00:04:04,875
What sort of terrible incident?

50
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:12,041
I advise not probing too much.

51
00:04:13,958 --> 00:04:17,416
I've gotta go.
Stay with him till I return.

52
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:18,791
Understood.

53
00:04:19,458 --> 00:04:20,625
Thanks.

54
00:04:44,875 --> 00:04:46,000
Ai...

55
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:54,708
Aqua is with the Ichigo Production Co.,

56
00:04:54,791 --> 00:04:56,958
where Ai once belonged.

57
00:04:58,333 --> 00:05:03,958
He and his twin sister's guardian
is agency president Miyako Saitoh.

58
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:09,333
His sister just relaunched
Ai's old idol unit, B-Komachi.

59
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:15,750
Both twins have an inordinate
obsession with Ai.

60
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:19,208
What if somewhere her child
is alive and well?

61
00:05:19,291 --> 00:05:23,416
As a child, he witnessed
a terrible incident.

62
00:05:24,708 --> 00:05:28,083
Ai died a violent and tragic death.

63
00:05:29,291 --> 00:05:34,083
If that's something that you
had to witness as a child...

64
00:05:36,166 --> 00:05:37,833
my heart breaks for you.

65
00:05:39,416 --> 00:05:40,833
Take it easy, Akane!

66
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:44,125
I'm not your enemy.

67
00:06:03,416 --> 00:06:04,500
What's wrong?

68
00:06:10,083 --> 00:06:11,083
Akane?

69
00:06:13,791 --> 00:06:17,750
I just had a horrifying thought.

70
00:06:22,708 --> 00:06:23,958
But I'm...

71
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:29,000
here for you no matter what.

72
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:36,875
Whatever pain you carry,
I want to bear it with you.

73
00:06:39,541 --> 00:06:41,291
What's this about?

74
00:06:44,458 --> 00:06:49,333
Just a "what if" scenario that
my wild imagination concocted.

75
00:06:53,291 --> 00:06:56,375
Can we explain the character this way?

76
00:06:56,458 --> 00:07:00,625
It does seem a departure
from the original.

77
00:07:00,708 --> 00:07:02,291
But it links to Episode 4.

78
00:07:03,333 --> 00:07:05,291
Any objections, Sensei?

79
00:07:06,833 --> 00:07:08,583
Nope, it's fine by me.

80
00:07:10,041 --> 00:07:14,458
Then we can print up Episode 3.
Good work, everyone.

81
00:07:15,208 --> 00:07:17,333
-Good work.
-Good work.

82
00:07:17,875 --> 00:07:20,250
When will you finish Episode 4?

83
00:07:22,583 --> 00:07:24,541
Day after tomorrow.

84
00:07:24,625 --> 00:07:28,750
Great, then I'll head back to the set.
Good luck.

85
00:07:32,791 --> 00:07:35,916
We went all out with Episode 3.

86
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:40,500
Need a break before moving on?

87
00:07:40,583 --> 00:07:41,625
Yes.

88
00:07:43,541 --> 00:07:44,958
Track 12.

89
00:07:46,583 --> 00:07:48,750
And action.

90
00:07:56,541 --> 00:07:59,583
Just because of this, you...

91
00:07:59,666 --> 00:08:00,833
Cut. Again.

92
00:08:01,333 --> 00:08:02,583
Cut.

93
00:08:05,541 --> 00:08:06,541
Director.

94
00:08:09,291 --> 00:08:11,416
Can we wrap this scene?

95
00:08:12,041 --> 00:08:16,458
We're running behind,
and need to edit Episode 1.

96
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,291
Bring eye drops.

97
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:24,041
Eye drops.

98
00:08:24,416 --> 00:08:25,416
Thank you.

99
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,125
-Once more.
-Sorry.

100
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:35,333
Try not to take it so hard.

101
00:08:36,708 --> 00:08:40,916
Mr. Kindaichi always asks for
a lot from actors.

102
00:08:41,666 --> 00:08:46,666
What kind of an actor am I
if I can't meet his demands?

103
00:08:47,416 --> 00:08:50,583
It's clear I just don't have any talent.

104
00:08:52,958 --> 00:08:57,166
If you don't feel you have the talent,
why do it?

105
00:08:57,791 --> 00:09:01,666
Is it because you like acting?
Or the money?

106
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:06,625
You wouldn't understand if I told you.
So I won't.

107
00:09:07,708 --> 00:09:11,041
I'm asking because I want to understand.

108
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,041
Say I told you my purpose...

109
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:30,291
was to murder someone? Then what?

110
00:09:33,416 --> 00:09:36,791
What if there was someone in the industry

111
00:09:38,208 --> 00:09:42,000
I'm seeking out so I can kill him?

112
00:09:46,041 --> 00:09:48,208
Then I'd kill him with you.

113
00:09:52,041 --> 00:09:57,166
I trust you have a good reason
for wanting that person dead.

114
00:09:58,791 --> 00:10:01,041
If you plan to bear that sin...

115
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:03,916
I want to bear it with you.

116
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:11,375
Don't take murder so lightly.

117
00:10:11,458 --> 00:10:15,208
I'm prepared to be that kind
of girlfriend for you.

118
00:10:17,291 --> 00:10:21,916
Even if we keep it strictly
a business relationship.

119
00:10:23,916 --> 00:10:25,833
That's not a normal way to be.

120
00:10:26,916 --> 00:10:29,791
I'm an actress. None of us are normal.

121
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,791
You may be right.

122
00:10:57,125 --> 00:11:00,083
Despite no shortage of setbacks...

123
00:11:00,166 --> 00:11:02,666
Tokyo Blade finally aired.

124
00:11:02,750 --> 00:11:05,041
I'm on my way now.

125
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:07,583
